## Slash Commands

Reusable commands available via `.cursor/commands/`:
- `/validate-scaffold` - Validate OS structure
- `/scaffold-os` - Regenerate scaffold
- `/kb-first-answer` - Enforce KB gate before responding
- `/create-kb-snippet` - Generate KB snippet in standard format
- `/handoff` - Emit formal handoff contract
- `/create-execution-tool` - Scaffold new Python tool
- `/create-execution-workflow` - Scaffold new workflow
- `/failure-triage` - Standard failure response protocol
- `/eval-maturity` - Run or request evaluation tooling
- `/plan-build-self-improve` - Execute plan→build→self-improve loop

## Context Exclusion

Files in `.cursorignore` are excluded from context by default (original-repo/, marked-for-deletion/, caches, logs, .env files).

